A bricklayer, ThankGod Emmanuel of Sauka-Kahuta area of Minna has been arrested by the Niger State Police Command for allegedly killing his co-worker over N47,000. The suspect who was apprehended by a team of policemen attached to Tundun Wada Division was said to have killed one Tita Komla, of the same address with digger. Our Correspondent in Tuesday learnt that the deceased’s brother, Tete Joe of Katampe Abuja, had earlier reported that his brother was working with the suspect in his construction company at Sauka-kahuta. He claimed that the suspect had called him on phone to notify him that his brother (Komla) had been killed by unknown persons. It was further gathered that the suspect engaged his victim in physical combat and killed him with a digger, robbed him of his N47,000 and dumped his body inside the gutter. The suspect told our Correspondent that he killed Komla with a digger in order to take his money adding that “Komla did not know I wanted to rob him of his money. “I killed him so that nobody will know that I stole his N47,000, I used digger to inflict injuries on his head and he died instantly. “I least suspected that police will identify me as the one that killed the deceased. Well, it’s really unfortunate. ” Confirming the incident, the Command’s Public Relations Officer, Muhammad Abubakar, said the suspect confessed to have committed the crime. Abubakar also said that the suspect inflicted injuries on the head of his victim and made away with his money, adding that the suspect would be arraigned before Court soon.